The paper deals with a theoretical problem in graph drawing, specifically the tradeoffs between curve complexity and area of RAC drawings. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Computational Geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves algorithms and complexity analysis, which could also place it in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The problem of RAC drawings also has connections to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper's focus on improving previous upper bounds suggests that it could also belong to the Scientific Computing (cs.SI) sub-category.
